message.content:
To find out how many test tubes were needed for each of the other two experiments, we can set up an equation based on the information given:

Total number of test tubes = (number of experiments) x (test tubes per experiment)
8 = 3 x (test tubes per experiment)

Now, we can solve for the test tubes per experiment:

Test tubes per experiment = 8 / 3
Test tubes per experiment = 2.67

Since we cannot have a fraction of a test tube, we can round up to the nearest whole number:

Test tubes per experiment = 3

So, each of the other two experiments required 3 test tubes.
